message.content: We have that $2 \cdot k = 5$, so $k = \frac{5}{2}$. The $12$th term is $2 \cdot\frac{5}{2} \cdot\frac{2}{5} \cdot\frac{5}{2} \cdot\frac{2}{5} \cdot\frac{5}{2} \cdot\frac{2}{5} \cdot\frac{5}{2} \cdot\frac{2}{5} \cdot\frac{5}{2} \cdot\frac{2}{5} \cdot\frac{5}{2}=\boxed{\frac{5}{2}}.$
